<li id="cite_note-114"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-114">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://roerichmongoliamonthly.wordpress.com/2011/07/30/vol-7-prof-s-bira-portrait-of-a-mongol-hero-2/">"Roerich Mongolia Monthly Vol 7: Prof. S. Bira, Portrait of a Mongol Hero"</a>. roerichmongoliamonthly.wordpress.com. 2011. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20181016165551/https://roerichmongoliamonthly.wordpress.com/2011/07/30/vol-7-prof-s-bira-portrait-of-a-mongol-hero-2/">Archived</a> from the original on 16 October 2018.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Roerich+Mongolia+Monthly+Vol+7%3A+Prof.+S.+Bira%2C+Portrait+of+a+Mongol+Hero&amp;rft.pub=roerichmongoliamonthly.wordpress.com&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Froerichmongoliamonthly.wordpress.com%2F2011%2F07%2F30%2Fvol-7-prof-s-bira-portrait-of-a-mongol-hero-2%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAgni+Yoga" class="Z3988"></span><br />«The painting  "Rigden Djapo" or "<a href="/wiki/King_of_Shambhala" class="mw-redirect" title="King of Shambhala">King of Shambhala</a>" is one of the many paintings created by <a href="/wiki/Nicholas_Roerich" title="Nicholas Roerich">Nicholas Roerich</a> during his residence in <a href="/wiki/Ulaanbaatar" title="Ulaanbaatar">Ulaanbaatar</a> in 1926-1927. This painting was presented by Roerich to the Mongolian government in 1927. Its survival was in doubt for many years. It was rediscovered in 1958 at Ulaanbaatar during the Prof. <a href="/wiki/George_de_Roerich" title="George de Roerich">George de Roerich</a> visit with Prof. <a href="/wiki/Shagdaryn_Bira" title="Shagdaryn Bira">Shagdaryn Bira</a> as guide.»</span>
